      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI (construct stiffness, N/mm) is directly specified in the F1717 standard and is the regulatory submission metric. Secondary QoI (peak screw stress) is mechanistically linked to fatigue failure mode relevant to clinical performance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
